This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as relation extraction and classification. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of low dimensional embedding space, which is a common technique in NLP. 

The paper also involves the use of crowdsourcing and inter-annotator disagreement, which are common themes in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). 

Furthermore, the paper discusses the improvement of a multi-class relation classifier, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Finally, the paper involves the propagation of human annotation signals, which is related to the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with the organization and retrieval of information from large datasets.
